France to Raise 250 Million Euros With CO2 Tax, Figaro Says

-- B y   L a u r e n c e   F r o s t
-- 
2011-09-27T16:47:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/france-to-raise-250-million-euros-with-co2-tax-figaro-says.html
The French government plans to
raise 250 million euros in its 2012 budget with a one-time CO2
tax on companies including Electricite de  France , Le Figaro
reported on its Web site. The tax will be applied at rates
between 0.08 percent and 0.12 percent of revenue, the French
daily said, without citing sources.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Laurence Frost at 
 lfrost4@bloomberg.net  